{
  "text": "In Fig. 1(a) columns of round cells represent the before and after terms in a temporal association sequence [CITATION_1] . We see here excitatory neurons obeying the standard Hebbian learning rule [CITATION_2] , the synapses between the columns reflecting the joint probability of the events (independent of time sequence or causality), but the simplified graphic should not be taken as precluding connections within a columnindeed the columns are shown separate only for didactic purposes and all units are activated by \"words\".",
  "correct_citation": {
